Package com.panda.dataframe

Class DataFrame

java.lang.Object
com.panda.dataframe.DataFrame
public class DataFrame
extends java.lang.Object
Core data structure, grouping DataCols.

Supports basic operations over rows and columns.

    • selectCols

      public DataFrame selectCols​(java.lang.String from, java.lang.String to)
      Returns a new DataFrame composed of the columns between the specified from and to labels inclusive.

      If anyone of the two labels does not exist - returns empty DF. If from is placed at right of column with label to - returns empty DF. Otherwise, returns the DataFrame containing the required selection of columns.

      Parameters:
      from - - starting label
      to - - ending label
      Returns:
      the new DataFrame

    • selectCols

      public DataFrame selectCols​(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> labels)
      Returns a new DataFrame composed of the columns associated to the specified labels. Returns an empty DF for non-existent, null labels.
      Parameters:
      labels - - list of labels
      Returns:
      the new DataFrame

    • selectRows

      public DataFrame selectRows​(java.lang.String from, java.lang.String to)
      Returns a new DataFrame composed from the rows between the specified from and to indexes inclusive.

      If one of the two indexes does not exist - returns empty DF. If from is placed below the index to - returns empty DF. Otherwise, return the DataFrame containing the required selection of rows.

      Parameters:
      from - - starting index
      to - - ending index
      Returns:
      the new DataFrame

    • selectRows

      public DataFrame selectRows​(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> indexes)
      Returns a new DataFrame composed from the rows associated to the specified indexes. If indexes' list is not valid - returns an empty DataFrame.
      Parameters:
      indexes - - list of indexes
      Returns:
      the new DataFrame
